# GORM Nullable Foreign Keys

Optional foreign key fields **must** use a pointer type (`*string`, `*uuid.UUID`, etc.), never a plain `string`.

A plain `string` field in Go defaults to `""`. GORM writes this as an empty string, not `NULL`. Any subsequent lookup using that empty value (e.g. `GetServerInstance("")`) will fail with:

```
ERROR: invalid input syntax for type uuid: "" (SQLSTATE 22P02)
```

## Pattern

```go
// ❌ BAD — defaults to "" in Go, stored as empty string, not NULL
ServerInstanceID string `gorm:"index"`

// ✅ GOOD — defaults to nil in Go, stored as NULL
ServerInstanceID *string `gorm:"index"`
```

## Migrations

When adding a nullable FK column via migration, also clean up any existing empty strings from prior data:

```sql
UPDATE matches SET server_instance_id = NULL WHERE server_instance_id = '';
```

## Checking in code

When reading a nullable FK, guard before dereferencing:

```go
if match.ServerInstanceID != nil && *match.ServerInstanceID != "" {
    si, err := models.GetServerInstance(*match.ServerInstanceID)
    // ...
}
```
